% First lets understand what a Document is in Hyland Terms:
% Document
% The Document class is the root object for all documents stored in OnBase.

% A Document is classified as any object in OnBase regardless of its File Format. For example, an image and PDF are both considered an OnBase Document.

% Notable Properties
% There are several properties that are worth noting and are commonly used when working with Documents

% Property

% Description

% ID

% Returns the ID assigned to the Document at the time of import or creation.

% Name

% Returns the full display name of the Document. Also known as the AutoName String.

% CreatedBy

% Returns the OnBase User who created or imported the Document.

% DateStored

% Returns the Date and Time the Document was created or imported into OnBase.

% DocumentDate

% Returns the Date and Time of the Document Date.

% DefaultFileType

% Returns the FileType configured within DocumentType configuration.

% DocumentType

% Returns the DocumentType to which a Document was imported or created.

% Status

% Returns the current status of the Document with OnBase.

% Notable Methods
% There are several methods that are worth noting and are commonly used when working with Documents

% Property

% Description

% CreateDocumentPropertiesModifier

% Creates a modifier object that is used to update attributes on a Document.

% LockDocument

% Locks the Document to a single OnBase User to prevent other users or processes from overwriting or making conflicting changes to the Document.

% Refresh

% Flushes the internal cache of the Document and reloads the Document information from the database.

