Executing Queries
Either of two methods can be used to query documents:

Simple Document Lookup
The GetDocumentByID method queries based on Document Handle.

Advanced Document Lookup
The DocumentQuery method returns documents based on specific criteria: Document Type, Document Type Group, Keywords and Full Text constraint.

Simple Document Lookup
To perform a simple document lookup, based on the Document Handle, use Application.Core object’s GetDocumentByID() method:

C#
1
2
3
4
5
Document document =  unityApplication.Core.GetDocumentByID(DOCUMENT_ID);
if(document == null)
{
  throw new Exception("Document not found.");
}
Advanced Document Lookup
To perform a more advanced lookup, utilize the DocumentQuery class. This class provides developers with the ability to look for documents that meet a certain set of criteria. The steps for defining and executing a document query are:

Create the DocumentQuery object.

C#
1
DocumentQuery docQuery = unityApp.Core.CreateDocumentQuery();
  Note

A new DocumentQuery object should be created by the above method for each unique query that is performed.

Add criteria to limit the results of the query.

DocumentType and/or a DocumentTypeGroup
Adding a document type and/or to the query will restrict the returned documents. If the DocumentTypeGroup is specified, the query will extend to all the DocumentTypes that are assigned to that DocumentTypeGroup. If no DocumentTypeGroup is specified, individual DoucmentTypes can be added to the DocumentQuery for a more granular query search.

