  Important

The KeywordOperator and KeywordRelation enumerators only work if the KeywordType is assigned to all DocumentTypes used in the query. If the KeywordType is not assigned to a DocumentType in the query, unexpected results will occur.

  Note

It is possible for a query to return multiple instances of the same item. When applying multiple Keyword search parameters, if a Document has more than one Multi-Instance Keyword Type Group record associated with it where separate records satisfy separate search parameters, the Document will be returned again for each occurrence of a match.

Executing the query has two options that are available, Execute and ExecuteQueryResults. Both methods require the maximum number of documents to retrieve though vary in their capabilities and implementation.

  Note

ExecuteQueryResults is the preferred method of querying for documents and should be used whenever possible.

Execute Method
This is a legacy method of executing document queries and does not provide the functional and performance capabilities offered by the ExecuteQueryResults function. This method returns ALL documents up to the maximum documents requested upon execution.

On execute, the developer must specify the maximum number of documents to retrieve. This method returns a DocumentList which contains a list of document objects that meets the query criteria.

C#
1
2
3
long maxDocuments = 100;

DocumentList docList = docQuery.Execute(maxDocuments);
Iterate through the list of document results.

C#
1
2
3
4
foreach (Document document in docList)
{
  // perform work on each document here
}
ExecuteQueryResults Method
ExecuteQueryResults offers the same capabilities as the Execute method but also provides the built-in ability to page query results (for increased performance) and specify DisplayColumns to return with the query result. DisplayColumns give the developer the following flexibility:

By default, display columns configured for a custom query are received without additional effort.

Alternatively, display columns can be manually specified to return with the query by Keyword Type and/or generic document properties.

Display column information can be manipulated within the query result without having to return and process all Keyword data on a document.

Unlike the Execute method, the ExecuteQueryResults method allows the developer to request and receive DisplayColumns on the query. These can be Keyword Types or generic DisplayColumnTypes

