You can add keywords that are not assigned to a Document Type for the document query. If keywords are added, the Unity API will not apply those restrictions on those Document Types, and the document query result may return more documents than expected. You should always verify that the keywords added to the document query are configured for the Document Type being queried before adding them to the query.

Document Query Retrieval Options
The method for setting DocumentRetrievalOptions can vary by the method of query execution. The RetrievalOptions property can be set on the DocumentQuery object if using either the Execute or ExecuteQueryResults methods; optionally DocumentRetrievalOptions can be set on an overload of the Execute method.

DRO overload options
Load Keywords
By default, document keyword data is not returned with documents during the document query function. As such keyword data is only requested and returned for a document when its keyword data is accessed programmatically through the API. DocumentRetrievalOptions can be set to override this default and allow the developer to return document keyword data at the time of querying.

